Name: Capability
Documentation:
A capability represents an ability that an active structure element, such as an organization,
person, or system, possesses.

Name: Course Of Action
Documentation:
A course of action is an approach or plan for configuring some capabilities and resources of the
enterprise, undertaken to achieve a goal.

Name: Resource
Documentation: A resource represents an asset owned or controlled by an individual or organization.

Name: Business Actor
Documentation: A business actor is a business entity that is capable of performing behavior

Name: Business Collaboration
Documentation:
A business collaboration is an aggregate of two or more business internal active structure
elements that work together to perform collective behavior

Name: Business Event
Documentation:
A business event is a business behavior element that denotes an organizational state change. It
may originate from and be resolved inside or outside the organization

Name: Business Function
Documentation:
A business function is a collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria
(typically required business resources and/or competences), closely aligned to an organization,
but not necessarily explicitly governed by the organization.

Name: Business Function
Documentation:
A business function is a collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria
(typically required business resources and/or competences), closely aligned to an organization,
but not necessarily explicitly governed by the organization.

Name: Business Function (copy)
Documentation:
A business function is a collection of business behavior based on a chosen set of criteria
(typically required business resources and/or competences), closely aligned to an organization,
but not necessarily explicitly governed by the organization.

Name: Business Interaction
Documentation:
A business interaction is a unit of collective business behavior performed by (a collaboration of)
two or more business roles

Name: Business Interface
Documentation:
A business interface is a point of access where a business service is made available to the
environment.

Name: Business Object
Documentation: A business object represents a concept used within a particular business domain

Name: Business Process
Documentation:
A business process represents a sequence of business behaviors that achieves a specific outcome
such as a defined set of products or business services.

Name: Business Process
Documentation:
A business process represents a sequence of business behaviors that achieves a specific outcome
such as a defined set of products or business services.

Name: Business Process (copy)
Documentation:
A business process represents a sequence of business behaviors that achieves a specific outcome
such as a defined set of products or business services.

Name: Business Role
Documentation:
A business role is the responsibility for performing specific behavior, to which an actor can be
assigned, or the part an actor plays in a particular action or event

Name: Business Service
Documentation: A business service represents an explicitly defined exposed business behavior

Name: Contract
Documentation:
A contract represents a formal or informal specification of an agreement between a provider and
a consumer that specifies the rights and obligations associated with a product and establishes
functional and non-functional parameters for interaction

Name: Product
Documentation:
A product represents a coherent collection of services and/or passive structure elements,
accompanied by a contract/set of agreements, which is offered as a whole to (internal or
external) customers.

Name: Representation
Documentation: A representation represents a perceptible form of the information carried by a business object

Name: Application Collaboration
Documentation:
An application collaboration represents an aggregate of two or more application components that
work together to perform collective application behavior.

Name: Application Component
Documentation:
An application component represents an encapsulation of application functionality aligned to
implementation structure, which is modular and replaceable. It encapsulates its behavior and
data, exposes services, and makes them available through interfaces.

Name: Application Event
Documentation: An application event is an application behavior element that denotes a state change

Name: Application Function
Documentation:
An application function represents automated behavior that can be performed by an application
component

Name: Application Interaction
Documentation:
An application interaction represents a unit of collective application behavior performed by (a
collaboration of) two or more application components.

Name: Application Interface
Documentation:
An application interface represents a point of access where application services are made
available to a user, another application component, or a node.

Name: Application Process
Documentation:
An application process represents a sequence of application behaviors that achieves a specific
outcome.

Name: Application Process (copy)
Documentation:
An application process represents a sequence of application behaviors that achieves a specific
outcome.

Name: Application Service
Documentation: An application service represents an explicitly defined exposed application behavior

Name: Data Object
Documentation: A data object represents data structured for automated processing

Name: Artifact
Documentation:
An artifact represents a piece of data that is used or produced in a software development process,
or by deployment and operation of an IT system.
(A technology object represents a passive element that is used or produced by technology
behavior.)

Name: Communication Network
Documentation:
A communication network represents a set of structures and behaviors that connects computer
systems or other electronic devices for transmission, routing, and reception of data or data-based
communications such as voice and video.

Name: Device
Documentation:
A device is a physical IT resource upon which system software and artifacts may be stored or
deployed for execution.

Name: Distribution Network
Documentation: A distribution network represents a physical network used to transport materials or energy

Name: Equipment
Documentation:
Equipment represents one or more physical machines, tools, or instruments that can create, use,
store, move, or transform materials.

Name: Facility
Documentation: A facility represents a physical structure or environment

Name: Material
Documentation: Material represents tangible physical matter or physical elements

Name: Node
Documentation:
A node represents a computational or physical resource that hosts, manipulates, or interacts with
other computational or physical resources.

Name: Path
Documentation:
A path represents a link between two or more nodes, through which these nodes can exchange
data or material.

Name: System Software
Documentation:
System software represents software that provides or contributes to an environment for storing,
executing, and using software or data deployed within it.

Name: Technology Collaboration
Documentation:
A technology collaboration represents an aggregate of two or more nodes that work together to
perform collective technology behavior.

Name: Technology Event
Documentation: A technology event is a technology behavior element that denotes a state change.

Name: Technology Function
Documentation:
A technology function represents a collection of technology behavior that can be performed by a
node.

Name: Technology Interaction
Documentation:
A technology interaction represents a unit of collective technology behavior performed by (a
collaboration of) two or more nodes.

Name: Technology Interface
Documentation:
A technology interface represents a point of access where technology services offered by a node
can be accessed.

Name: Technology Process
Documentation:
A technology process represents a sequence of technology behaviors that achieves a specific
outcome.

Name: Technology Process (copy)
Documentation:
A technology process represents a sequence of technology behaviors that achieves a specific
outcome.

Name: Technology Service
Documentation: A technology service represents an explicitly defined exposed technology behavior.

Name: Assessment
Documentation:
An assessment represents the result of an analysis of the state of affairs of the enterprise with
respect to some driver.

Name: Constraint
Documentation: A constraint represents a factor that prevents or obstructs the realization of goals.

Name: Driver
Documentation:
A driver represents an external or internal condition that motivates an organization to define its
goals and implement the changes necessary to achieve them.

Name: Goal
Documentation: A goal represents a high-level statement of intent, direction, or desired end state for an organization and its stakeholders.

Name: Meaning
Documentation:
Meaning represents the knowledge or expertise present in, or the interpretation given to, a core
element in a particular context.

Name: Outcome
Documentation: An outcome represents an end result that has been achieved

Name: Principle
Documentation: A principle represents a qualitative statement of intent that should be met by the architecture

Name: Requirement
Documentation: A requirement represents a statement of need that must be met by the architecture.

Name: Stakeholder
Documentation:
A stakeholder is the role of an individual, team, or organization (or classes thereof) that
represents their interests in the outcome of the architecture.

Name: Value
Documentation: Value represents the relative worth, utility, or importance of a core element or an outcome.

Name: Deliverable
Documentation: A deliverable represents a precisely-defined outcome of a work package

Name: Gap
Documentation: A gap represents a statement of difference between two plateaus

Name: Implementation Event
Documentation:
An implementation event is a behavior element that denotes a state change related to
implementation or migration

Name: Plateau
Documentation:
A plateau represents a relatively stable state of the architecture that exists during a limited period
of time.

Name: Plateau
Documentation:
A plateau represents a relatively stable state of the architecture that exists during a limited period
of time.

Name: Work Package
Documentation:
A work package represents a series of actions identified and designed to achieve specific results
within specified time and resource constraints.

Name: capability
Documentation:
Capability Architecture provides an organizing framework for change activity and the development of effective architecture roadmaps
realizing capability increments.
o current capability,
o target capability, and
o capability increments (work packages and projects to be grouped within managed portfolios and programs)

Name: segment
Documentation:
Segment Architecture provides an organizing framework for operational and change activity and allows for direction setting and the
development of effective architecture roadmaps at a program or portfolio level.

Name: strategic
Documentation:
Strategic Architecture provides an organizing framework for operational and change activity and allows for direction setting at an executive
level.
